name: Saugeen District Secondary School
directions: Back of the school by the 4 doors, up the stairs. Take a left and you’ll see the sign for the single person restroom
comment: Usually the staff don’t let strangers in. Act like you’re just in looking for a friend. FYI the upper floor can be accessed by an elevator. The restroom has bars for support and a full sanitary system

comment: The basement bathrooms have a gender neutral sign on them. If the chapel is open, they should be open.

name: Ulster Museum
comment: Free entry to museum. Toilet located on ground floor.

name: Boston GLASS
directions: queer and trans youth of color (up to age 25) drop in space that also provides services. JRI is on the right side of the street on Amory St (they also have single stall bathrooms) keep walking down Amory St and turn right when you hit Amory Ave and walk along the building towards the empty and turn right on the corner of the building and you'll see the glass door entrance

name: Square One Shopping Centre Food Court

comment: Requires “buzzing in” on an intercom

name: Milly’s
directions: It’s towards the back of the restaurant. The signs should point the way. There’s two restrooms and they’re both gender neutral and single stalled.
comment: You’ll probably have to buy something at the restaurant before going to the bathroom. Also, the bathroom has a bar for people who need assistance in sitting down and getting back up, but I didn’t label it accessible because the hallway and bathroom itself is so narrow/small, that it’s definitely not accommodating for those with wheelchairs. Canes and maybe walkers could fit, though.
